<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="494" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2023]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Pale brown with green shade (green in life). Head, parts of pronotum, scutellum, femora and forewing venation, pale brown, crown with one apical (sometimes absent) and one basal median small spots, fuscous.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2023]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Crown without median carina, pronotum without median carina but with short lateral carina confined to anterior transverse depressed area.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2023]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis box="[199,363,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Tergum of pygofer short, anteriorly produced in lateral view; dorsal margin sinuated in middle, lobe posteriorly rounded, ventral margin concave in middle, ventral process narrowed distally, exceeding dorsal margin of pygofer. Subgenital plate long narrow, more than five times as long as wide at base, dorsolateral margin with 2–3 short, stout macrosetae and numerous long hair-like setae. Connective Y-shaped, with arms longer than stem. Style S-shaped, apophysis curved with series of microsetae, and apically rounded with a few rugae. Ventral process of aedeagus with stem as long as distal arms, each arm rather of uniform width for most part and distally slightly rounded apically, aedeagus membranous, atrium elongate, shaft short, broad at base and narrowed towards apex, surface of shaft spiculate, apex of shaft concave in anterior view, gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2023]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis box="[199,389,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite longer than wide, narrowed posteriorly beyond basal 0.33, posterior margin almost straight with rounded lateral margins with the inner margin notched. First and second pair of valvulae as in 
<figureCitation box="[151,279,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 90" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1873,1896]" captionTargetBox="[204,1390,208,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[191,1396,193,1853]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 90. Female ovipositor in species of Signoretia. 80 – 83. S. sahyadrica sp. nov. 80. First pair of valvula; 81. First pair of valvula apex; 82. Second pair of valvula; 83. Apex of second pair of valvula. 84 – 86. S. lunglei sp. nov. 84. Ovipositor, lateral view; 85. Apex of first pair of valvula; 86. Apex of second pair of valvula. 87 – 90. S. maculata Baker; 87. First pair of valvula; 88. Apex of first pair of valvula; 89. Second pair of valvula; 90. Apex of second pair of valvula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167197/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Figs 80–83</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
