<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="494" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2023]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1961,1986]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name alludes to the 
<collectingRegion box="[717,808,1962,1985]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Western" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Western</collectingRegion>
Ghats (
<emphasis box="[901,1002,1962,1986]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Sahyadri</emphasis>
, Samskrit). Specimens of this species were collected from various localities from this mountain range.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="495" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[321,474,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahyadrica">
<emphasis box="[321,474,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">S. sahyadrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has bluntly rounded apices of the arms of the ventral process of the aedeagus as in the case of 
<taxonomicName box="[235,346,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaya">
<emphasis box="[235,249,188,211]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[263,346,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">malaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the former differs in having much straighter and broader arms in lateral view and the pygofer ventral process more acute and shorter compared to the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
